abstract: Two classic penitentiary dramas — Don Siegel’s “Riot in Cell Block 11” and George Hill’s “The Big House” — come to DVD.
snippet: Two classic penitentiary dramas — Don Siegel’s “Riot in Cell Block 11” and George Hill’s “The Big House” — come to DVD.
lead_paragraph: Are prison movies the most escapist of Hollywood genres — or the least? Don Siegel’s explosive “Riot in Cell Block 11,” released on its 60th anniversary in an extras-laden Criterion dual-format edition, is one penitentiary movie in which busting out is never an option.

abstract: Tom Steyer, a billionaire environmental activist, wants to help climate change become a major issue in the next presidential campaign by raising awareness in pivotal states.
snippet: Tom Steyer, a billionaire environmental activist, wants to help climate change become a major issue in the next presidential campaign by raising awareness in pivotal states.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Tom Steyer, a billionaire environmental activist from California, wants to blast the issue of climate change to the front lines of American politics. His “super PAC,” NextGen Climate, will spend about $100 million this year to influence several Senate and governor’s races in which climate change could play a major role.

abstract: Tom Steyer, whom Republicans have depicted as a one-man special interest group, plans to raise $100 million to run campaigns on climate issues and efforts to block the Keystone XL pipeline.
snippet: Tom Steyer, whom Republicans have depicted as a one-man special interest group, plans to raise $100 million to run campaigns on climate issues and efforts to block the Keystone XL pipeline.
lead_paragraph: Tom Steyer, the billionaire climate activist, recently contributed $5 million to a “super PAC” dedicated to keeping Democrats in control of the United States Senate, cementing his alliance with the party as the 2014 campaign swings into high gear.
